	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real person — maybe you. The apartment that's quiet at the end of the day. The wedding invitation that stings a little. The family gathering where someone asks, again, if you've met anyone. The dating app you open out of duty more than hope. The lie that whispers your real life starts the day you stop being single.</p><p>None of this means something is wrong with you. It means you're human, living in a world that treats marriage as the finish line and singleness as a waiting room — and that's a weight no one was meant to carry. There is a Father who sees you fully in this exact season, and He has something to say about who you already are to Him.</p>`}
