	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel different the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's love isn't a passing feeling — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that loneliness can't uproot.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I know this season. I see the quiet evenings, the empty chair, the question you keep getting asked, the ache you carry when no one's looking. And I want you to hear Me over all of it: you are not behind, and you are not incomplete. You are Mine, and I love you right now — not the married you, not the someday you. You.</p><p>You don't have to wait for a partner to begin your real life, and you don't have to earn My love to keep it. I made you on purpose, I set the lonely in family, and I am your home. When the loneliness comes, come to Me — I'll quiet you with My love and fill the place you thought only someone else could fill. You are fully Mine and fully loved, today."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for singles`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these single hearts — every one carrying more than anyone sees. Let them hear Your whisper above the noise — the loneliness, the pressure, the lie that life only starts when they marry. Let them encounter Your love — not as a waiting room, but as a Father's delight — and know they are Your beloved, fully loved, apart from their relationship status.</p><p>Give them contentment that isn't pretending, but the deep rest of knowing You are enough. Father, fill the quiet evenings with Your nearness, set the lonely in true family, and steady them in the longing. Where there is the ache for a partner, meet them; where there is fatigue and discouragement, give fresh hope; and where they wonder if You have forgotten them, remind them that You know the plans You have for them — plans for a future and a hope.</p><p>Let them know there is no shame in this season, that they are fully home in You, and that nothing can separate them from Your love. Let them know You, their Father, as their portion and their reward. And may they wake up every single day knowing they are loved by their heavenly Father.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
