	faqs={[
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about being single?`, answer: `The Bible treats singleness not as a lesser status but as a season the Father can fill and even use. 1 Corinthians 7:32-35 describes singleness as a gift of undivided devotion to God, and Isaiah 54:5 says your Maker calls Himself your husband — a faithful love that never leaves. Far from being incomplete, you are the Father's beloved right now. Read and hear these passages free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for loneliness?`, answer: `Psalm 68:6 (God sets the lonely in family), Zephaniah 3:17 (your Father is in your midst and rejoices over you), Psalm 16:11 (fullness of joy in His presence), Psalm 73:25-26 (God is the strength of your heart and your portion), and Romans 8:38-39 (nothing can separate you from His love) all speak straight to loneliness. Read and listen to them free, with audio, in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Does God have a plan for single people?`, answer: `Yes. Jeremiah 29:11 says God knows the plans He has for you — plans for a future and a hope — and that includes this season, not just the one after it. Your worth and your purpose were never on hold until you marry. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet God as a Father who delights in you and has good plans for your life right now. Read it free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
